                        <em>Electronic</em>. Unit operating and capacity factor information demonstrating that the unit qualifies as a peaking unit or gas-fired unit, as defined in §72.2 of this chapter, and NO<sub>x</sub> correlation test information, including:
                        <ol type="A">
                            <li>
                                Test date;
                            </li>
                            <li>
                                Test number;
                            </li>
                            <li>
                                Operating level;
                            </li>
                            <li>
                                Segment ID of the NO<sub>x</sub> correlation curve;
                            </li>
                            <li>
                                NO<sub>x</sub> monitoring system identification;
                            </li>
                            <li>
                                Low and high heat input rate values and corresponding NO<sub>x</sub> emission rates;
                            </li>
                            <li>
                                Type of fuel; and
                            </li>
                            <li>  To document the unit qualifies as a peaking unit, current calendar year or ozone season, capacity factor data as specified in the definition of peaking unit in §72.2 of this chapter, and an indication of whether the data are actual or projected data.</li>
                        </ol>
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <em>Hard Copy</em>.
                        <ol type="A">
                            <li>
                                A protocol containing methods used to perform the baseline or periodic NO<sub>x</sub> emission test; and
                            </li>
                            <li>
                                Unit operating parameters related to NO<sub>x</sub> formation by the unit.
                            </li>
                        </ol>

                    </li>
                </ol>
            </li>
            <li>   For each gas-fired unit and diesel-fired unit or unit with a wet flue gas pollution control system for which the designated representative claims an opacity monitoring exemption under <a href="~/Part75/75.14" style="text-decoration: none">§75.14</a>, the designated representative shall include in the hard copy monitoring plan the information specified under <a href="~/Part75/75.14" style="text-decoration: none">§75.14</a>(b), (c), or (d), demonstrating that the unit qualifies for the exemption.</li>
            <li>
                For each monitoring system recertification, maintenance, or other event, the designated representative shall include the following additional information in electronic format in the monitoring plan:
                <ol type="i">
                    <li>
                        Component/system identification code;
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        Event code or code for required test;
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        Event begin date and hour;
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        Conditionally valid data period begin date and hour (if applicable);
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        Date and hour that last test is successfully completed; and
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        Indicator of whether conditionally valid data were reported at the end of the quarter.
                    </li>
                </ol>
            </li>
            <li>
                For each unit using the low mass emission excepted methodology under <a href="~/Part75/75.19" style="text-decoration: none">§75.19</a> the designated representative shall include the following additional information in the monitoring plan that accompanies the initial certification application:
                <ol type="i">
